"Jeanneau M., Pichant P.","The impact of regulations on automotive manufacturing [Impact des contraintes réglementaires sur la construction automobile]",2004,"Revue de Metallurgie. Cahiers D'Informations Techniques","101","1",,"57","66",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-10744231202&partnerID=40&md5=d6e64d5ed3071626876a2ce61d7236ec","ATS; Arcelor Auto","Jeanneau, M., ATS; Pichant, P., Arcelor Auto","The automobile is still the favored means of locomotion in Europe. Easy to use and a freedom satisfier make it indispensable in our daily lives. A yet the car is at the same time accused by playing a major role in atmospheric population and global warning of the earth by the greenhouse effect, being the main source of harmful noise and danger, and thus obliging lawmakers to react and make it evolve under regulatory pressure. The proposed of this article is to determine the current situation and posture in terms of law and regulations concerning it and to describe the solutions offered by steel.",,"Accident prevention; Air pollution control; Environmental impact; Gas emissions; Greenhouse effect; Industrial wastes; Recycling; Regulatory compliance; Standards; Waste disposal; Engine emissions; Pollutant emissions; Valorization; Automobile manufacture",,,,,,,"ATS",,,,,,,,00351563,,REMEA,,"French","Rev Metall",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-10744231202
